MsmqTransportElement Class

In this Article

Represents the binding element used to specify the queuing communication properties for a Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) service that uses the native MSMQ protocol.

Remarks

The MsmqTransportBindingElement enables the user to set the properties of the queued communication channel. The queued communication channel uses MSMQ for its transport.

This binding element is the default binding element used by the MSMQ standard binding (NetMsmqBinding).

Properties

  • BindingElementType

    Gets the binding type.

    public override Type BindingElementType { get; }

    Property Value

    • Type

      A Type object that represents the binding type.

  • MaxPoolSize

    Gets or sets an integer that specifies the maximum size of the pool that contains internal MSMQ message objects.

    public int MaxPoolSize { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Int32

      An integer that specifies the maximum size of the pool that contains internal MSMQ message objects.

    Remarks

    The internal MSMQ message object pool is used to avoid allocations of these objects when sending and receiving messages. The maximum pool size is a performance tuning parameter. The default value is 8.

  • Properties
    protected override System.Configuration.ConfigurationPropertyCollection Properties { get; }

    Property Value

    • ConfigurationPropertyCollection

      To be added.

  • QueueTransferProtocol

    Gets or sets an enumeration value that indicates the queued communication channel transport that this binding uses.

    public System.ServiceModel.QueueTransferProtocol QueueTransferProtocol { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • QueueTransferProtocol

      A QueueTransferProtocol enumeration value that indicates the transport used for message delivery between queue managers.

    Remarks

    MSMQ does not support Active Directory addressing when using SOAP Reliable Messaging Protocol, so do not set QueueTransferProtocol to QueueTransferProtocol or QueueTransferProtocol when UseActiveDirectory is set to true.

  • UseActiveDirectory

    Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether queue addresses should be converted using Active Directory.

    public bool UseActiveDirectory { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Boolean

      true if queue addresses should be converted using Active Directory; otherwise, false.

    Remarks

    MSMQ queue addresses can consist of path names or direct format names. With a direct format name, MSMQ resolves the queue name using DNS, NetBIOS, or IP. With a path name, MSMQ resolves the queue name using Active Directory.

    By default, the Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) queued transport converts the URI of a message queue to a direct format name. By setting the UseActiveDirectory property to true, an application can specify that the queued transport should resolve the computer name using Active Directory rather than DNS, NetBIOS, or IP.
